the casualty rate was exacerbated by the lack of ejection seats in early series meteors ; the ground - breaking high speed that the aircraft was capable of meant that , during the bailing out process , pilots were typically subject to high g forces hindering movement and the effect of slipstream winds ; there was also a greater likelihood of the pilot striking the horizontal tailplane .

